---
id: org.dxos.plugin.code
name: CodePlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A plugin for AI-assisted Composer plugin development. Hosts authored DEUS specs
(`.mdl` files), couples them to a `CodeProject`, and provides a Coder blueprint
that lets the assistant verify a spec and dispatch a build agent. The build
agent itself is a separate EDGE service (not part of this PR); phase 1 ships
the schema, blueprint, settings, credential wiring, and stub operations only.

The plugin replaces the previous `plugin-spec` (rename) and reuses
`react-ui-editor`'s `Editor.Root` / `Editor.Toolbar` / `Editor.Content`
together with the existing `mdl()` CodeMirror extensions instead of a bespoke
editor implementation.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

## Types

```mdl
type Spec
  desc: |
    A DEUS spec document. Carries `.mdl` content and a human-readable name.
    Existing typename `org.dxos.type.spec` is preserved across the rename.
  fields:
    name?: string
    content: Ref<Text>          # mdl source
```

```mdl
type CodeProject
  desc: |
    A coding project. Pairs a name with a Spec used to drive code generation.
    Typename `org.dxos.type.codeProject`.
  fields:
    name?: string
    spec: Ref<Spec>             # the DEUS spec authored for this project
```

```mdl
type Settings
  desc: |
    Plugin settings (plugin-scoped, not per-space). Reactive.
    The Anthropic API key itself is NOT stored here — it lives in an
    AccessToken ECHO object with source `anthropic.com`, accessed via
    the composer credentials API.
  fields:
    endpoint?: string           # URL of the EDGE build service (phase-2 wiring)
```

## Components

```mdl
component CodeArticle
  desc: |
    Article surface for a Spec. Renders its content in `react-ui-editor`'s
    Editor primitives (`Editor.Root` / `Editor.Toolbar` / `Editor.Content`)
    with the existing `mdl()` / `mdlBlockDescription` / `mdlLint` /
    `mdlComplete` CodeMirror extensions for `.mdl` syntax, lint, completion.

    The toolbar carries a Spec | Code tab toggle, contributed via
    `EditorToolbar.customActions` (an `Atom.Atom<ActionGraphProps>`). The
    active tab is local component state.
  props:
    role: string
    subject: Spec
    attendableId?: string
  state:
    view: spec | code           # which tab is active
  slots:
    overlay?: ReactNode         # phase-2 build status overlay
  actions:
    selectView(view: spec | code)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Editor.Toolbar                      │
    │  [B][I][U] … │ Spec │ Code │ search │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Spec view: Editor.Content           │
    │   (mdl() + mdlLint + mdlComplete)   │
    │                                     │
    │ Code view: placeholder              │
    │   "Build output will appear here"   │
    └─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component CodeSettings
  desc: |
    Settings surface contributed via `AppPlugin.addSettingsModule`. Lets the
    user paste/clear an Anthropic API key. The key is persisted to an
    AccessToken (source `anthropic.com`) in the user's HALO space; reads/
    writes go through the composer credentials API, not Settings.
  props:
    settings: Settings
  state:
    apiKey?: string             # bound to AccessToken.token
  actions:
    saveApiKey(value: string)
    clearApiKey()
```

## Services

```mdl
service Credentials
  desc: |
    Composer credentials API (`@dxos/functions/services/CredentialsService`).
    Used by `CodeSettings` to read/write the Anthropic API key as an
    AccessToken with source `anthropic.com`.
  ops:
    getCredential(query: { service: string }) → ServiceCredential
    queryCredentials(query: { service: string }) → ServiceCredential[]
```

```mdl
service BuildAgent
  desc: |
    The remote EDGE service that runs the Claude Agent SDK to generate
    Composer plugins from a Spec. Out of scope for this PR — phase 1 only
    declares the contract surface. Will live in `dxos/edge`.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    verify(spec: Spec) → { ok: bool, messages: string[] }
    build(project: CodeProject) → { runId: string, status: string }
```

## Operations

Phase-1 stubs: both ops are wired into the blueprint as tools but return
deterministic placeholder values until the EDGE service exists.

```mdl
op verifySpec
  desc: |
    Static verification of a DEUS spec — lint + structural checks. Phase-1
    stub returns `{ ok: true, messages: [] }`. Will eventually delegate to
    BuildAgent.verify.
  input:
    spec: Ref<Spec>
  output: { ok: bool, messages: string[] }
  effects: [echo:read]
  requires: [Database]
  note: |
    Operation key: `org.dxos.function.code.verify-spec`.
    Exposed as a blueprint tool on CoderBlueprint.
```

```mdl
op runBuildAgent
  desc: |
    Dispatches a build of the project via the EDGE BuildAgent. Phase-1 stub
    returns `{ status: "queued" }` without performing any work.
  input:
    project: Ref<CodeProject>
  output: { status: queued | running | succeeded | failed }
  effects: [echo:read, http]
  requires: [Database, Credentials]
  note: |
    Operation key: `org.dxos.function.code.run-build-agent`.
    Phase-2: reads the Anthropic API key via Credentials and POSTs to the
    EDGE BuildAgent endpoint configured in Settings.endpoint.
```

## Blueprints

```mdl
type CoderBlueprint
  desc: |
    Blueprint key `org.dxos.blueprint.coder`. Provides the assistant with a
    system prompt explaining how to drive a CodeProject — author/refine the
    Spec with the user, run `verifySpec` before dispatching a build, and call
    `runBuildAgent` to kick off generation. Tools: verifySpec, runBuildAgent.
  fields:
    key: org.dxos.blueprint.coder
    tools: [op:verifySpec, op:runBuildAgent]
    instructions: prose         # see CoderBlueprint.instructions section
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Rename plugin-spec → plugin-code

  req F-1.1: Package renamed `@dxos/plugin-spec` → `@dxos/plugin-code`.
  req F-1.2: Directory renamed `packages/plugins/plugin-spec` → `packages/plugins/plugin-code`.
  req F-1.3: Plugin id renamed `org.dxos.plugin.spec` → `org.dxos.plugin.code`.
  req F-1.4: SpecPlugin → CodePlugin; SpecArticle → CodeArticle.
  req F-1.5: Spec ECHO type retains typename `org.dxos.type.spec` (no migration).
  req F-1.6:
    when: composer-app loads after rename
    then: existing Spec objects continue to render; no schema migration needed
```

```mdl
feat F-2: CodeProject type

  req F-2.1: New ECHO type `CodeProject` with typename `org.dxos.type.codeProject`.
  req F-2.2: Fields `name?: string`, `spec: Ref<Spec>`; both reactive.
  req F-2.3:
    when: user creates a CodeProject from the navtree
    then: an empty Spec is created and referenced by the new CodeProject
  req F-2.4: CodeProject registered via `addSchemaModule` and `addMetadataModule`.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: CodeArticle uses react-ui-editor

  req F-3.1: CodeArticle uses `Editor.Root` + `Editor.Toolbar` + `Editor.Content`
             from `@dxos/react-ui-editor` instead of a bespoke `useTextEditor` setup.
  req F-3.2: The existing `mdl()`, `mdlBlockDescription`, `mdlLint`, `mdlComplete`
             extensions are passed to the editor.
  req F-3.3:
    when: a Spec is opened
    then: its `content` is editable with markdown + .mdl block highlighting
  req F-3.4: Toolbar exposes a Spec | Code tab toggle via `customActions`.
  req F-3.5:
    when: user clicks "Code"
    then: editor area is hidden and a placeholder ("Build output will appear here") is shown
  req F-3.6:
    when: user clicks "Spec"
    then: editor area is restored and focus returns to the document
  req F-3.7: Active tab is local component state (not persisted).
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Settings + credentials

  req F-4.1: `Settings` schema mutable, with optional `endpoint: string`.
  req F-4.2: Settings registered via `AppPlugin.addSettingsModule`.
  req F-4.3: A `CodeSettings` container renders an API-key input.
  req F-4.4:
    when: user enters an API key and saves
    then: an `AccessToken` is upserted with `source: "anthropic.com"`, `token: <value>`
          via the composer credentials API
  req F-4.5:
    when: user clears the key
    then: the matching AccessToken is removed
  req F-4.6: API key value is never stored in `Settings`.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Coder blueprint

  req F-5.1: A blueprint with key `org.dxos.blueprint.coder` is contributed
             via `addBlueprintDefinitionModule`.
  req F-5.2: Tools include op:verifySpec and op:runBuildAgent.
  req F-5.3: System instructions describe the Coder role:
              author/refine spec with user, run verifySpec, then runBuildAgent.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Stub operations

  req F-6.1: op:verifySpec defined and handler returns `{ ok: true, messages: [] }`.
  req F-6.2: op:runBuildAgent defined and handler returns `{ status: "queued" }`.
  req F-6.3: Both handlers are contributed via `addOperationHandlerModule`.
  req F-6.4: Both operations resolve from blueprint tool calls without error.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Rename preserves Spec compatibility
  given: a space already containing a Spec object created by plugin-spec
  when: the renamed plugin-code is loaded
  then:
    - the Spec object is queryable
    - opening it renders CodeArticle with the same content
    - typename remains `org.dxos.type.spec`
```

```mdl
test T-2: Create CodeProject
  given: composer-app with plugin-code loaded
  when: user invokes "Create CodeProject" from a space
  then:
    - a new CodeProject object is created with default name
    - a new empty Spec is created and referenced via `project.spec`
    - opening the project surfaces the linked Spec via CodeArticle
```

```mdl
test T-3: Editor renders mdl content
  given: a Spec containing an mdl fenced block
  when: CodeArticle mounts
  then:
    - markdown is decorated by `decorateMarkdown()`
    - the mdl block body is highlighted by `mdlBlockDescription`
    - lint and completion sources are wired
```

```mdl
test T-4: Toolbar tab toggle
  given: a CodeArticle is open showing the Spec view
  when: user clicks the Code tab
  then:
    - the editor content is hidden
    - the Code placeholder ("Build output will appear here") is visible
  when: user clicks the Spec tab
  then: the editor content is visible again
```

```mdl
test T-5: Save API key persists AccessToken
  given: CodeSettings is open and no AccessToken exists for `anthropic.com`
  when: user enters a key and clicks save
  then:
    - an AccessToken with `source: "anthropic.com"` and the entered token is created
    - the input shows the masked persisted value on next render
```

```mdl
test T-6: Clear API key removes AccessToken
  given: an AccessToken exists for `anthropic.com`
  when: user clicks clear
  then:
    - the AccessToken is removed
    - subsequent `CredentialsService.getCredential({ service: "anthropic.com" })` rejects
```

```mdl
test T-7: Blueprint registers tools
  given: composer-app with plugin-code loaded
  when: AppCapabilities.BlueprintDefinition is queried for `org.dxos.blueprint.coder`
  then:
    - the blueprint is present
    - its tool set includes verifySpec and runBuildAgent
```

```mdl
test T-8: Stub operations resolve
  given: an assistant chat with the Coder blueprint loaded
  when: the assistant invokes verifySpec on a Spec
  then: the call returns `{ ok: true, messages: [] }`
  when: the assistant invokes runBuildAgent on a CodeProject
  then: the call returns `{ status: "queued" }`
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap
    literals?: UnionList
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap
    state?: FieldMap
    slots?: FieldMap
    actions?: ActionMap
    emits?: EventMap
    layout?: CodeBlock
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap
    output?: TypeExpr
    errors?: ErrorMap
    effects?: EffectList
    requires?: ServiceList
    note?: Prose
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
